cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 85 miles NNE of Grand Cayman and 195 miles WSW of Camaguey, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: moving northeast, forecast to cross central Cuba tonight, then turn north-northwest and approach/clip South Florida and the Florida Keys late Sunday–Monday before bending westward into the eastern Gulf of Mexico

weather_observation.impacted_coast: South Florida and Florida Keys; minor surge possible as far north as the Georgia coast (Altamaha Sound)
weather_observation.wind: Low (only an 8% cumulative chance of tropical-storm-force winds by day 5)
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor coastal inundation of 2–3 ft possible along the southeast GA coast, including Brunswick, mainly Monday–Tuesday due to prolonged onshore flow as Eta passes well to the south
weather_observation.rainfall: Showers in outer rain-bands could produce 1–2 inches; widespread 4-inch totals are not expected
weather_observation.other_hazards: Hazardous surf and rip currents along the Georgia beaches
